@Basab Ray.........................in response to your face book complaint vide memo no. F/B-79(M) dt. 24.05.13. We like to inform you that PWD has already been started the Widening and Strengthening Project Work of existing Road from Taratola More to Joka Tram Depot (7.16km) via James Long Sarani in the District of 24pgs. (South) under CRF (Job No- CRF/WB/2012-2013/35) from 11.03.2013 for the interest of public service. So, the matter of tree cutting is under consideration of PWD authority.

          Farther, you are requested to contact with PWD authority for better clarification about the tree cutting in James Long Sarani.  Thanks.
.

@Srikumar Chatterjee ......... In response to your facebook complaint vide F/B No- 05(M) dated 08.01.13., an enquiry was made under the supervision of O/C SPL. Raid/TP, Lalbazar, during enquiry your complaint have been established against conductor of P/Bus bearing Registration No- WB04E 7548, of Rt. no- 228 for misbehaviour.
   Accordingly the said conductor was prosecuted under the section of law vide SPL Raid Compound case  No-013566.
This is for your information.

@Khalid Anwar.... in reference your facebook complaint ref. F/B no- 1291on 28.08.12 and F/B no-1210 dt. 18.08.12, this is to inform you that the entire strech from 155 CR Avenue to 157 C.R. Avenue ( Stretch partly end at the back side of M.G. Road Metro Station) is a no parking zone inclusive of M.M. Barman Street. Any violation regarding parking norms are being dealt promptly and strictly through
prosecution under M.V. Act. As the area is adjacent to Mechhua Fruit market , it is often noticed that traders often bring that purchase articles on CR Avenue to get various means of transports. Any obstruction to the carriageway is being prosecuted U/S 283 IPC. Total 129 number of vehicles were prosecuted under different section of M.V. Act and 283 IPC since from 01.08.12 to 31.09.12 in that area.
Regarding collection of money by hooligan as mentioned by you , nothing such come into the notice of the Officer of the Guard or the O/C, after observation of considerable period. Any further enquiry if needed may be contacted with the concerned P.S. However constant vigilance will be continued on the matter from the KTP jurisdiction.

@Debasish Dey.... in response your complaint vide memo no F/B- 1255 dt.
24.08.12, in the month of April,2012 the Hon'ble Supreme Court of India has strictly prohibited using of filmy glasses in motor vehicles where tinted glass is Motor Vehicle is allowed in conformity with the provision framed there  under rule100(2) CMVR,1989, sub rule(2) of rule 100 of the CMVR provides 70% visual light transmission(VLT) is required to be maintained at the front wind screen of the Motor Vehicle, where 50% VLT is required to be maintained at the side windows.
           In compliance with the said order, KTP may taking action U/S 100(2) CMVR/192 MVA read with 52 of MVA as and when noticed any violation of the norms stated herein above.

@Devashis Kuthari.... in response your complaint vide memo no F/B- 1100 & 1101 dt.07.08.12, enquiry was made by O/C Park Circus Traffic Guard, it could be learnt from enquiry that the said truck was kept by W.B. Excise  Department, after getting information, the concerned guard made and effort to parked in a single line parallel to the curb and usually they do not cause any obstruction to the normal flow of traffic.
          2nd, the photograph of the buses as shown are the school buses of C0ulcutta Boys School. These buses comes a little time before the school gives over and leaves during the rest of the day no buses stand there.
               However double line parking is not allowed . In the past week over such school bus was prosecuted for keeping in a double line. Since then no school bus seen to be parked in double line, but their single line parking is allowed for the brief period due to social compulsion.

@Biswabir Chatterjee .... in response your complaint vide memo no F/B- 1482 dt.11.09.12, you have lodge complaint without furnish any information about date and number of auto Rickshaw misbehaved with you.
          Further, you mentioned that one Sgt. joydeep Chatterjee stood there, but it could be learnt from concerned traffic guard that no such Sgt. exist at their Guard strength, and also none were reported to concerned guard about this type of incident.
        So, the concerned guard could not take any action from their end.

@Subhronath Mukherjee….. your FB complaint on18.07.2012 read….”The taxi driver simply refused me. When I said that my wife is seriously ill and needs urgent medical attention hence I am going to Apollo he still denied. Next I told him that I have to complaint to police in that case he told me "Hmm jan jan complaint korun ami to parar e taxi police er khunjtey subidha hobey" I felt really disgusted.” 
This is to inform you that Biswanath Jha the offending driver has been brought to book followed by prosecution and temporary suspension of license. Taxi No: WB04C 1339.“
Thanks and regards, from Team KTP.

@Maharshi Chakrabarti..... in reference your face book complaint (ref.memo no-777 dt. 10.07.12) regarding the worst position of entrance of Dhakuria flyover, a large number of crowd are use to cross the road near southern slope of Dhakuria Bridge. This is very dangerous for pedestrian traffic and also for vehicular traffic.
             Actually a proposal of extension of median divider of southern slope may be extend for 30 ft. approx and pedestrian barrier for 30 ft. approx on the both side on footpath of southern slope of Dhakuria Bridge to prevent people to stand there to get a bus is under consideration of sanction authority. The job will be taken up shortly.

                                                                        Thanks & regards.

@Deepanjan Ghosh…… your FB complaint against taxi-refusal on 25.07.2012 read……” I was refused on the 24th of July, 2012, at 21:10 hrs, on Camac Street, opposite Shantiniketan Building, by taxi number WB04 E 6113” 

This is to bring to your kind notice that Sunil Singh, The offending driver has brought to book. He has been prosecuted and his licence has been temporarily suspended. Here is the photograph of the offender.

Thanks and Regards, Team KTP.

@Mehboob Rahman (F/B 869 dated 18.07.12) this is to inform you that buses are being compelled to ply along Bus Bay along Khidderpur Road by our officers, whenever they are on duty on these places. 
Moreover the violation of the Bus lane may take place whenever the sector officers are not present at that particulars place due their patrolling to other places.
Moreover, the officer have been asked to remain vigilant and to prosecute against the violators under proper section of law.

@Aditya Sharma----- in ref. your face book complaint vide memo no- F/B- 1029 dt- 01.08.12, this is to inform you that as per your face book complaint it is necessary to lodge on MCR at the concerned PS. However we checked the concerned PS, no case has been recorded there against the vehicle no- WB04D2331 on 27.07.12.
           In traffic point of view we will keep sharp vigil to prevent such incident in future and take necessary action against the offender.
           Thanking you for sharing this type of observation. We should remain careful in future.

@Surendra Singh-----Ref:-F/B 524 dt 13 .06.12, With the above reference ,enquiry was made under the supervision of O/C South  T.P Guard, enquiry revels that Northern side of Royd Street is free parking Zone. And southern side of Royd street is "No parking Zone" area.
              Action have already been taken for keeping vehicles in No parking Zone.
However, O/C South T.P Guard instructed to Sector officers to keep strict vigil on Royd Street and make prosecution against vehicles parked at no parking zone.

@Dibantim Mukherjee 
In reference your face book complaint vide F/B 568 dated 22.06.12 inquiry was made through ADDL. O/C Garia Traffic guard it could be learnt from inquiry that Goria to Gol Park Auto Route are functioning properly on their schedule route without any break up journey within Goria area. 
                 However, President & Secretary of the Auto union Goria to Gol Park Rt. are  requested to inform the owner and the driver of the Auto not to take up break journey,   otherwise legal action will be taken for such illegal practice.

@Pankaj Vora 
 In Ref:-your face book complaint vide  F/B 730 &756 dated 08.07.12   enquiry was made by O/C Bhowanipur Traffic Guard , it could be learnt from enquiry that (4) four number Matadoor stand at Lee Rd. and Elgin Rd crossing is there since long and it is authorized KMC fee parking zone.
    In the above circumstances you are requested to contact with KMC authority for the said matter.

@Subrata Banerjee ….Ref your face book complaint regarding use of Neon light-F/B 620(A) Dated 28.06.12 , this is to inform you that the nature of complaint which under provision of Rule 106 of CMVR,1989 provided that lamp should be fitted in every motor vehicle while being driven in public place as per Law provide in Rule 105 of CMVR,1989.
    It is mention that as per sub-rule(1) of Rule 106 of CMVR,1989 provided that no lamp showing a light to the front shall be used on any Motor Vehicles unless such lamp is so constructed, fitted and mention that the beam of light emitted –
(a) is permanently deflected down wards to such an extent that it is not capable of dazzling any person whose eye position is (A) at a distance of 8(eight) meters from the front lamp.

@Salim Ali (Ref.F/B-277 dated 22.03.12) your face book complain sent to the concerned authority for taking necessary action regular vigilance maintaining for avoiding illegal parking. 
        Regarding remove the encroachment (snack shops etc) join raid with local  PS to be conducted after getting necessary permission from competent authority.
       No parking board already fixed northern side of Netaji Nagar from N S C Bose road to Bastuhara and some board will be fixed letter on and strict is maintain in this connection.
